sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as Dev/Ops User (Browser or roxctl)
    box Internal Enterprise Network
    participant Sensor as RHACS Sensor (Secured Cluster)
    participant Central as RHACS Central (Hub Cluster)
    participant Zscaler as Zscaler SSLO Engine
    participant Proxy as Corporate Web Proxy
    end
    box Public Internet
    participant External as External Feeds (definitions.stackrox.io)
    end

    %% FLOW 1: Outbound Egress Inspection Flow
    rect rgb(230, 242, 255)
        Note over Sensor, External: FLOW 1: Outbound Egress Inspection Flow (Vulnerability & Driver Updates)
        Central->>Zscaler: HTTPS Request to download CVE data [Port 443]
        Note over Zscaler: Decrypts Payload & Performs Security Inspection
        Zscaler->>Proxy: Re-encrypts payload & proxies forward (Signed by Zscaler CA)
        Proxy->>External: Routes connection out to StackRox/Red Hat endpoints [Port 443]
        External-->>Proxy: Returns raw database update payload / VEX feeds
        Proxy-->>Zscaler: Forwards payload back into network
        Zscaler-->>Central: Delivers verified payload (Succeeds because Zscaler CA is injected into ACS)
    end

    %% Tunneling note for Sensor
    rect rgb(255, 255, 255)
        Note over Sensor, Central: Secure Sensor-to-Central Tunneling Note
        Sensor->>Central: Sensor requests kernel modules over secure gRPC tunnel [Port 443]
        Note over Central: Central initiates internet download on Sensor's behalf via Flow 1
    end

    %% FLOW 2: Ingress User Access Flow
    rect rgb(242, 230, 255)
        Note over User, Central: FLOW 2: Ingress User Access Flow (Portal & CLI Management)
        User->>Central: Connect to ACS Portal UI or execute CLI API command [Port 443]
        Central-->>User: Presents default Self-Signed Certificate
        Note over User: Browser triggers untrusted warning OR roxctl uses '--insecure-skip-tls-verify'
    end